4.text: Amaya and Manuka are at the zoo with their parents.

5.text: Amaya: Mother, I like to see the birds.

6.text: Father: Amaya, first we will see the fish. We are following the map.

7.text: Amaya: Alright father. Where are the fish?

8.text: Manuka: Now we are at the entrance. Fish are in the first block.

9.text: Mother: Here is the first block. This is the aquarium. It’s dark here. Amaya, hold my hand.

10.text: Amaya : Mother, these fish are very nice. What are they called?

11.text: Father : Let’s see the board there. Oh! They are clown fish. They live in Indian and Pacific Oceans. There are arapaima fish in the next tank.

12.text: Amaya: They are very big. Brother, there are a lot of fish here. Did we miss any?

13.text: Manuka: No, we didn’t . The birds are in the third, fourth and fifth blocks. Let’s go there.

14.text: Amaya: Wonderful! I love birds. Let’s go there soon.

15.text: Manuka: Sister, those are macaws.They are very colourful.
